description.narrative: (Malawi): USAID's Malawi Scholarship Program (MSP) improves availability of human resources for health. The MSP provides scholarships to Malawians to pursue undergraduate and Master's programs in specific areas at universities and colleges in Malawi, Africa, and in the United States.FY 2015 activities will:-Provide scholarships for 138 students within Malawi to pursue pre-service training in the areas of nursing and midwifery and pharmacy technician preparation;-Support 37 Master's degree students in public health, maternal and child health, nutrition, and family planning/reproductive health; and-Provide additional 200 nursing scholarships between 2016 and 2020. These activities will help mitigate the severe human resource shortage in Malawi's health sector and strengthen the capacity of the Ministry of Health, the Department of Nutrition and HIV/AIDS and local Malawian organizations to provide quality health care services to the population.
